# module keyword

Authoritative contract for HINT directive keywords and their shared rendering context. Parser, compiler, and concrete keyword modules read this file once per compiled context and reuse it through the `KeywordContract` reference.

# entity Directive

Every canonical top-level directive accepted after case and alias normalization.

- 'read' | 'lang' | 'deps' | 'build'
- 'app' | 'lib' | 'namespace' | 'module' | 'res' | 'rule'
- 'entity' | 'function' | 'ui' | 'action'
- 'good' | 'bad' | 'example' | 'test' | 'notes'

# entity RawBlock

A parsed directive block passed from the parser to the keyword renderer.

- directive: {Directive}
  the canonical directive that selects `&#123;directive&#125;.ts.hint`
- name: string | undefined
  the optional target parsed from the directive header
- body: string
  everything below the directive header until the next top-level directive, `---`, or EOF
- sourcePath: string
  the HINT file that declared the block
- sourceKind: 'baseline' | 'direct' | 'file'
  the block's location in the documented cascade, from folder baseline to target file

# entity ReadRef

The parsed run-time file reference declared by `# read &#123;glob&#125; as [name]`.

- name: string
  the explicit alias, or the deterministic reference name derived from the path when the alias is omitted
- glob: string
  the file path or glob pattern inside braces
- description: string
  the block body explaining the referenced source's architectural role

# entity KeywordInput

The compiler context bound before a keyword template renders.

- block: {RawBlock}
  the parsed block selected for rendering
- directive: {RawBlock}.directive
- name: {RawBlock}.name
- body: {RawBlock}.body after all single-brace cross-references have been resolved
- reads: Map<string, {ReadRef}>
  all run-time file references in the assembled context, keyed by reference name

# rule

- A keyword template receives {KeywordInput}; it must not redeclare the common directive, name, and body fields.
- The template filename must be `&#123;directive&#125;.ts.hint`, and its stem must equal the canonical directive in {KeywordInput}.directive.
- Directive matching is case-insensitive. Documented aliases normalize before {RawBlock} creation:
    - language to lang; dependencies to deps; pipeline and ci to build
    - application to app; library to lib; ns and package to namespace; resource to res
    - struct, model, and schema to entity; func, fn, and method to function
    - screen, view, page, and component to ui; macro and automation to action
    - rules, constraint, and constraints to rule
    - pattern, patterns, best-practice, and best-practices to good
    - antipattern, antipatterns, forbidden, and prohibit to bad
    - sample and demo to example; verify, spec, and criteria to test
    - note, comment, todo, fixme, and draft to notes
    - argument to arg; returns to return
- `@include` is the only `@` directive. It is expanded before tokenization and never becomes a {RawBlock}.
- `# read` is a structural directive and remains a {RawBlock}; the parser also records its {ReadRef} for cross-reference validation.
- The fenced markdown under the template's `# entity Output` block is the exact section shape returned to the compiler.
- {{double-brace}} tokens are compiler interpolation points. They are distinct from HINT's {single-brace} cross-references, which resolve before the keyword template executes.
- {{#field}}...{{/field}} is a conditional block. Include its content only when the named field is non-empty.
- {{^field}}...{{/field}} is an inverse conditional block. Include its content only when the named field is empty.
- Preserve the developer's markdown body verbatim after cross-reference resolution unless the keyword's own rules explicitly require structured sub-block rendering.
- Keyword templates describe output shape and constraints only. Shared loading, binding, interpolation, and section assembly logic belongs to the compiler.
